(1 comment)
Looking for a "Why" in here. Why specifically do we need this new feature?

This is already in downstream to give name in the IBM specific format, if this option is not given the name wil be in default format. Moved it here for better testing with downstream and needed feature
Ack

So someone is calling this API with a dump, and that dump has to match the appropriate regex and POS rules. How do we ensure whoever created this dump followed the rules that are now configured at build time in this repo? Before this, it was hard coded so everyone was on the same page with that hard coded rule.
Yes that hardcoded name was derived as part of the initial discussion of the BMC dump but that name is only for plain master and needs to be customized based on the organizational specification
Ack

Since this is IBM specific requirement, better approach is to get IBM specific  Manager function in  dump/extension/IBM  folder , this will help to contain all IBM specific custom requirement definition with out changing common existing dump implementation.
Some thing similar to used for openpower dumps.
IBM specific is just an example and there is no impact on existing code apart from moving the hardcoded file format to meson

Code change is not in meson , based on your current approach , required changes in deport code , how you you are planing to share the meson defined format variable to  to dreport?

Another option you can look here is 
use obmcdump_ID_EPOCHTIME.EXT dump initially ( no change in dreport ) and once dump created, and after  properties extraction required for d-bus object creation , use name specific override function to rename the file and create the dump entry. This will less code chnages compared to proposed approch.

Now changing name will be done in the dreport script as part of the OEM specific part, instead of adding code for name change in the main dump code. Now the code is clean, otherwise a custom function to change the code needs to be called from main code and that will make it more complecated
And based on the requirements from several other platforms, there will be changes needed in the script, I think it is better to contain most of these changes in the script itself.

Another issue is serial number needs to be added to the dump name, which is found in the script, then there will be complications while restoring a custom-named dump file. so I think the best option is to handle it in the regular expression part.

Please answer my previous question "how you you are planing to share the meson defined format variable to to dreport?".

Also share the commit information used to enable this feature.
We can keep the same hardcoded name for the file since it is not known outside and while offloading it gets changed to whatever the external interface chooses
Regarding the question " "how you you are planing to share the meson defined format variable to to dreport?". I am expecting it should work the sameway as the hardcoded value is working now.
Abandoning this commit and the commit for reading the human readable timestamp from the filename.
No progress in review , removing from my list
